    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-10-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-10-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="62" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d62">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Thompson</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-10-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 25,
                            1893</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Gresham acknowledges Mr. Thompson’s telegram of the 24th, and remarks
                        that recognition by the United States of the insurgents as belligerents
                        would be an unfriendly act toward Brazil and a gratuitous demonstration of
                        moral support to the rebellion, the insurgents having not, apparently, up to
                        date established and maintained apolitical organization which would justify
                        such recognition on the part of the United States. He instructs him to
                        observe, until further advised, the attitude of an indifferent spectator,
                        and communicates to him the President’s expectation that he will transmit to
                        the Department all information bearing on events transpiring at Rio de
                        Janeiro and other ports of Brazil and espouse the cause of neither side.</p>
            </div>
